From: conda-forge recipe maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] Strip CLI-tool Requires-Dist entries + exclude sdist symlink

(1) Upstream lists `uv` and `git-annex` as `Requires-Dist` so that
`pip install xorq` bootstraps both CLI tools from PyPI. On conda-forge
they are packaged separately as native binaries (Rust and Haskell
respectively) and do not ship a Python `.dist-info/` directory, which
makes `pip check` report them as missing even though `$PREFIX/bin/uv`
and `$PREFIX/bin/git-annex` are present. Both are still declared in
the recipe's `run:` block, so the conda solver still pulls them in.

(2) The xorq sdist ships a symlink at
`python/xorq/common/utils/tests/conftest.py` →
`../../../backends/xorq_datafusion/tests/conftest.py`. On Windows the
extracted symlink dangles or becomes a text stub (depending on whether
the build agent holds SeCreateSymbolicLinkPrivilege), and hatchling's
wheel builder fails the `os.stat` with `WinError 123` ("The filename,
directory name, or volume label syntax is incorrect"). Exclude the
symlinked path from the wheel build — the target file
(`python/xorq/backends/xorq_datafusion/tests/conftest.py`) still
ships, so `pytest` discovery against an installed xorq still finds a
conftest for the xorq_datafusion backend tests.

--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -8,6 +8,7 @@
 # wheel ZIP).  By excluding here we ensure only force-include writes the files.
 exclude = [
     "python/xorq/env_templates/**",
+    "python/xorq/common/utils/tests/conftest.py",
 ]

 # .gitignore contains `.env.*` which hatchling treats as an exclusion pattern
@@ -54,10 +55,8 @@
     "prometheus-client>=0.22.1",
     "cryptography>=45.0.3",
     "strenum>=0.4.15 ; python_version <= '3.10'",
-    "uv>=0.7.20",
     "rich>=13.9.4",
     "click>=8.0",
-    "git-annex>=10.20250220",
     "gitpython>=3.1.46",
     "textual>=1.0.0",
     "filelock>=3.13",
